  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to document that taking part in this program is beneficial for
      the child, its parents and local professionals.

      The study hypothesis are:

      Intensive training will speed up the childs motor, cognitive and social development.

      Intensive habilitation will increase the childs family's empowerment Children having
      participated in this intensive habilitation will speed up their process of development
      further than children in the control group The cooperation between first and second line
      health service is strengthened by participation in the intensive habilitation program The
      professionals in the first line(community)in Norway that participates in this program
      increases their empowerment and motivation
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
